  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ZELA SA Solidarity Hub - Women Voices in Mining</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	Taking photos or pictures that tells the story of women voices for a better, safe responsible and gender sensitive artisanal and small-scale sector
2.	Documenting and sharing women voices through blogs. This exercise will encourage women artisanal and small-scale gold miners to write their own stories in local languages or English, and promote them via Ubumbano voice app, and other blog channels. 
3.	Capacity building training for women in the artisanal mining sector to take photos that tells a story, to document impact stories and to use social media to deliver their key messages to stakeholders such as government, business, parliament, media and development partners.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ZELA will support the process of amplifying the voices of artisanal miners in Bubi district in Southern Zimbabwe. With a targeted campaign of amplifying women artisanal miner&#x2019;s voices, it presents an opportunity for the district to be part of the development agenda and link up with others in Southern Africa through the SA Solidarity hub by practical use of the Ubumbano Voice App.</narrative>
  </description>
